The testing, followed by quarantine of people who tested positive and tracing of people who had contact with people who tested positive for SARS-CoV-2, gave a positive final result.
Researchers working in the Italian city of Vò, the site of the first COVID-19 death in Italy, conducted two rounds of testing on an entire population of 3,400 people, about 10 days apart.
About half of the people who test positive have no symptoms, and all cases found are quarantined.
With the travel restrictions in place, new infections are being eliminated completely.
