In a study by the National Health Commission (NHC) of China, men had a mortality rate of 2.8%, while women had a mortality rate of 1.7%.
Histopathological examination of postmortem lung samples showed diffuse alveolar damage with cellular fibromycoid exudate in both lungs.
Viral cytopathic changes are observed in pneumocytes.
The lung image resembles that of acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS).
